
The directory 'paper' contains the file 'cgr1-2.dvi' which is a dvi file
for the paper titled 

"A correlated basis set for non-adiabatic energy calculations
on diatomic molecules"

as submitted to J. Chem. Phys..  Nov. 13, 1998

The directory 'src' contains the source code for the program 'cgr1' 
which is described in in the paper above.

'sample-input' contains sample input files for H2+, H2 and LiH.

The code is for research purposes and should be used at your own risk.
Also, check the input files to be sure you are computing what you expect.

There is a makefile in the source directory that can be modified for your site.

Feel free to modify and use the code in any way you see fit.
However, if you do anything with this code please let me know.


Dr. Donald B. Kinghorn
University of Arizona
Dept. of Chemistry
Tucson AZ 85721

kinghorn@u.arizona.edu  

Enjoy!

